# Adaptive per-proof thread concurrency patch
#
# Status: APPLIED to node_modules (JS runtime patch)
#
# Patched: ~/.aztec/versions/4.1.3/node_modules/@aztec/bb-prover/dest/bb/execute.js
#
# ── What it does ──
#
# Replaces the hardcoded getAdaptiveConcurrency() with a configurable system:
#
#   1. Maps circuit name patterns -> dyadic sizes (log2 gate count)
#   2. Looks up thread count from PROVER_THREAD_MAP env var (or defaults)
#   3. Passes per-proof concurrency to both daemon (JSON protocol) and
#      process-per-proof (HARDWARE_CONCURRENCY env var) paths
#
# Default mapping (optimized for M3 Pro 18 GiB):
#   2^24 (RootRollup):        6 threads  (~11 GiB peak, single-agent only)
#   2^23 (CheckpointRoot):    4 threads  (~6 GiB peak, memory-sensitive)
#   2^22 (BaseRollup/Parity): 4 threads  (~2-3 GiB peak)
#   2^21 (Merge rollups):     3 threads  (~2.6 GiB peak)
#   2^20 (BlockRootEmpty):    2 threads  (~1.5 GiB peak)
#
# ── Configuration ──
#
# Override defaults via env var:
#   PROVER_THREAD_MAP="24:6,23:4,22:4,21:3,20:2"
#
# Format: comma-separated "dyadicSize:threadCount" pairs.
# Only specified sizes are overridden; unspecified sizes get no adaptive override
# (falls back to HARDWARE_CONCURRENCY).
#
# ── Backwards compatibility ──
#
# - If PROVER_THREAD_MAP is not set, uses built-in defaults
# - If a circuit type is not recognized, returns undefined -> falls back to
#   HARDWARE_CONCURRENCY env var (existing behavior)
# - If HARDWARE_CONCURRENCY is also not set, bb uses its own default
#
# ── Key fix from prior version ──
#
# CheckpointRootRollup was previously grouped with RootRollup at 6 threads.
# Now correctly mapped to 4 threads (2^23 = ~6 GiB peak), reducing memory
# amplification when running 3 agents concurrently.
#
# ── How to re-apply after npm install ──
#
# The patch modifies execute.js in-place. To re-apply:
#   1. Copy the getAdaptiveConcurrency block from this patch description
#   2. Or run: node scripts/apply-patches.js (if available)
#
# ── Diff summary ──
#
# Replaced lines 161-176 (old getAdaptiveConcurrency) with:
#   - _CIRCUIT_DYADIC_SIZE: pattern -> size mapping table
#   - _DEFAULT_CONCURRENCY_MAP: size -> thread count defaults
#   - _getThreadMap(): lazy parser for PROVER_THREAD_MAP env var
#   - getAdaptiveConcurrency(): two-step lookup (name -> size -> threads)
